The Small Scale Installations by Postcode are published by the Clean Energy Regulator (CER).

<br/><br/>CER publishes a number of reports in relation to the [CER REC Registry](http://www.rec-registry.gov.au/) information. The public Register of small-scale technology certificates (STCs) in the REC Registry allows users to search and view details of small-scale technology certificate creation.

<br/><br/>The postcode data shows small-scale systems by installation year. The Clean Energy Regulator will not provide any further analysis of the data provided.

<br/><br/>The postcode data includes information about 2,815,888 small scale installations grouped under 5 Small Generation Unit (SGU) categories:
<br/>
<ul>
<li>Solar Panel; </li>
<li>Wind; </li>
<li>Hydro; </li>
<li>Solar Water Heater – Solar; </li>
<li>Solar Water Heater – Air Sourced Pump</li>
</ul>
<br/>More information and raw data files are available here: [http://www.cleanenergyregulator.gov.au/RET/Forms-and-resources/Postcode-data-for-small-scale-installations](http://www.cleanenergyregulator.gov.au/RET/Forms-and-resources/Postcode-data-for-small-scale-installations)
